<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>emsenn.net</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/</link><description>Recent content on emsenn.net</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>frontmatter</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/frontmatter/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/frontmatter/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frontmatter&lt;/strong&gt; is a block of structured metadata placed at the top of a &lt;a href="markdown-file.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Markdown file&lt;/a&gt;, delimited by a pair of &lt;code&gt;---&lt;/code&gt; lines. The content between the delimiters is written in YAML (a human-readable data format) and provides machine-readable information about the document.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A typical frontmatter block looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;---
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;title&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Example Note&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;date-created&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;2025-06-15&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;tags&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; - &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;type/term&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;---
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Everything above the closing &lt;code&gt;---&lt;/code&gt; is metadata; everything below it is the document&amp;rsquo;s body content. Markdown processors and static site generators read the frontmatter to determine how to render, categorize, and link the document.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>link</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/link/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/link/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A reference from one markdown file to another, often encoded as a path.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Markdown file</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/markdown-file/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/markdown-file/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A plain-text document using markdown syntax plus optional YAML frontmatter.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>note</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/note/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/note/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A single markdown file within a vault, often treated as a thing or node.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>vault</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/vault/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/tech/domains/computing/domains/markdown/terms/vault/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A collection of markdown files treated as a linked knowledge base.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>